						<summary><p>#16. a) Gaṅgājaṭādhara temple of Govindapputtūr; b) ARE 1928–29, no. 160 (+ part 2, para 29); c) personally located; d) on the lowest part of the base of the northern façade; begins on the western side of the <foreign>gomukha</foreign> on the <foreign>ardha-maṇḍapa</foreign> and continues on the <foreign>antarala</foreign>; the last part is on the lowest part of the base of the eastern section of the sanctuary; e) regnal year 7 of Kōrājarājakesarivarman; f) Rājarāja I (<foreign>circa</foreign> 992 C.E.); g) there is no <foreign>svasti śrī</foreign> at the beginning of this inscription; many passages of this inscription remain illegible, and the translation is thus fragmentary.</p>

</summary>
